<P>AN ORATION, DELIVERED BEFORE THE SOCIETY OF CINCINNATI, HARTFORD, July 4, 1794.</P>
<P>BY ELIJAH WATERMAN.</P>
<Q>All governments labor under incurable disorders. The af|fairs of mortals are desperate: they will never know happiness, till philosophy takes them under her guidance.<BIBL>Plato.</BIBL></Q>
<Q>I am the light of the world.<BIBL>Christ.</BIBL></Q>
<P>PRINTED AT HARTFORD, BY HUDSON AND GOODWIN.</P>
<P>MDCCXCIV.</P>
</DIV1>
